[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man in court over charity worker's death

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has appeared in court charged with murdering a charity worker and the attempted murder of a 16-year-old boy.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Alyson Watt, who was 52 and worked for Barnardo's Scotland, died on Friday following an incident in Penilee Road in Paisley.
The teenage boy remains in a critical condition in hospital following the same incident.
Gary Brown, who is 54, made no plea or declaration and was remanded into custody at Paisley Sheriff Court.
